issue_comments.body:
I'd recommend that you use an enum instead of a define for the list of feature types, like

``` C
typedef enum {
    DISCID_FEATURE_READ = 1,
    DISCID_FEATURE_MCN,
    ...
} discid_feature_t;

int discid_supports_feature(discid_feature_t feature);
```

This gives you better type-checking in C.

While adding the bug report at http://tickets.musicbrainz.org/browse/LIB-29 I thought it would maybe be good to have the features enum usable as bit flags:

``` c
enum discid_feature {
  DISCID_FEATURE_READ = 1,
  DISCID_FEATURE_MCN = 2,
  DISCID_FEATURE_ISRC = 4,
};
```

That way we could create a read method accepting an `int features` flag list:

``` c
discid_read(disc, device, DISCID_FEATURE_MCN | DISCID_FEATURE_ISRC);
```

Don't know how we would deal with DISCID_FEATURE_READ, it wouldn't make much sense to set this. Maybe it would just be assumed implicitly.

